            "summary": "<p>Resistance bands do work — scientifically, there's no question. If you follow a structured program, do the right exercises with correct form, and stick to it for 8+ weeks, you will see arm toning results.</p><p>The \"if\" is the problem. In my test group, the resistance band users had the lowest 12-week consistency rate of any device. Not because the bands don't work — because using them correctly requires knowing which exercises to do, having space to do them, and showing up with intention every session. That's a lot of friction for a busy woman who just wants slimmer arms without disrupting her whole routine.</p>",
            "how_steps": "",
