            "grade": "C",
            "tone": "dark",
            "specs": "",
            "summary": "<p>I included two vibration-based arm devices in the test because of how aggressively they're marketed on social media. The claims range from \"EMS technology activates fat cells\" to \"passive workout while you relax.\" Let me translate: passive workouts don't build the muscle that produces arm definition.</p><p>Vibration does increase local circulation and can help with muscle relaxation and soreness — that part is real. But it doesn't create the muscle engagement required to change arm composition. In 12 weeks, zero participants in the vibration group showed measurable arm definition changes.</p>",
            "how_steps": "",
            "metrics": "",
            "testimonials": "",
            "pros": "",
            "cons": "",
            "bottom_line": "<p>Buy one as a relaxation tool if you want to. Don't buy it expecting toned arms. Those are two completely different products, and these vibration belts are only delivering on one of them.</p>",
